title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare LNIB Smith & Wesson Model 916T Field Grade 12 ga Pump Shotgun
postcontent:
.
Smith & Wesson Model 916T Field Grade 12 ga Pump Shotgun LNIB


The only S&W shotgun that was ever MADE IN USA. Not all 916T's were created equal. This one is a rare version of the 916T that has:

- Wildlife Scene (Duck in flight with Catails) Engraved in the Receiver
- Checkering in the Forearm and Grip
- White Line Spacers at the Recoil Pad and Pistol Grip Cap 
- Two-Bead Wavy Top Ventilated Rib.
- Correct O stamp Barrel (NO Recall) with Chrome Bore

This is the barrel that shipped with the gun, not a S&W recall replacement barrel, so the gun must have been a very late one with the revisions already in place. The barrel is 28" and Steel Shot Safe.


In all the years I have owned the gun I have never seen another one like it (I saw 'one' that was similar but did not have the correct barrel). Every other 916T I have seen was the plain jane version with no engraving, no checkering, no spacer's, if they had a VR at all it was a standard one, and all, but a handful, did not have the correct O stamped barrel which can be dangerous.


Barrel Markings on Left Side:

SMITH & WESSON - MODEL 916T
SPRINGFIELD, MA., - MADE IN U.S.A.

Right Side:

PROOF TESTED 12 GA.
- 3 INCH CHAMBER -
MODIFIED CHOKE


I bought the gun brand new many years ago. Fired 50~100 rounds. I have the original box, but cannot find the paperwork.


Please no message's quoting book value as this gun is simply not in the book with the feature's that it has. The book lists only the plain jane 916T with a potentially dangerous barrel. Even so, I am pricing this Deluxe 916T right in line with the book value of the plain jane 916T. Condition is an easy 98% or Excellent, depending on the book.


$250 firm or Trade up/down/even for Wood Field/Sporting/Hunting Long Guns, a .22 Auto Target Pistol, or a Large Caliber Revolver with 5" plus barrel for deer hunting. Can add cash.

May also trade for 28 squares of shingles, a truck stake bed (bed/rails only), motorcycle, lawn tractor, Gibson, Epihone or EPS electric guitar, vintage minibike, ?

title: For Sale:  WTS/T Tikka T3 Lite .270wsm / Bushnell Elite 3-9x50 with RainGuard
location: Orange County, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
I just cut the asking price!


This rifle is as close to new as they come. It was bought for my wife. I bore-sighted the scope & took a couple of shots to get on the paper — then she announced she wasn't hunting. I immediately stopped playing with it. (OK, I was more than a little "aggravated" as she could have said that before I bought the outfit. Previously she had said she didn't want to cary a heavy rifle, so I got the Tikka T3 Lite.) I can't say it's new & unfired, but I can say we've never hunted with it & it looks to be in perfect condition.

I've never seen a Tikka that didn't print a clover-leaf group or better & I have no reason to believe this would be any different. I had someone hand me a Tikka T3 that he said wouldn't group when we were shooting 2 weeks ago. I took 3 of his shells & put 3 shots into 100 yd target, producing a group that was less than 1/4" between centers. I then told him he needed to practice more because that's how the Tikka T3s shoot.

The .270 WSM is a great cartridge. It shoots flatter than a .25-06 or .270 Win. yet doesn't require a muzzle brake to shoot comfortably.

The Bushnell Elite scope is the same as we have on our .243 & I can speak to how well it works. The RainGuard works wonderfully & eliminates almost all fogging so you don't miss a shot because you exhaled as you picked up your rifle. The 3-9x50 will let you shoot way past legal light. It picks up light VERY well!

I've got about $700 in the outfit it but would listen to reasonable offers (cash or trade). I may sell at a loss but I will not give it away. This will be sold as it's become a personal sore spot (the joys of marriage), & it's taking up space in the safe. If it doesn't sell as a unit I will split it up. Let me know if you are interested and make your offer. This will be posted on several boards so it may sell quickly.

We can ship to your FFL but prefer face-to-face.


Things I'm looking for: quality 20-60x80mm spotting scope, 15x56 binoculars, quality rifle scopes (Swarovski, Nightforce, Zeiss, etc.); & accurate stainless rifles in: .243 Win, .338 magnum, .340 magnum, a 410 shotgun, and anything else "interesting" that's not junk. 

Yes, we are focussed on HUNTING arms and, no, we are not looking for pistols or more archery gear. Although we prefer stainless with composite stocks, we will consider blued steel with wood stocks if it's something we would want to cary hunting.

If we ship we'll split the costs.

It's still available in Orange County. Let's deal!
